b"Just in time for World Vegan Day, Chef Chloe Coscarelli showed us how to make a Vegan Pumpkin Marble Cake! It's the perfect addition to @chefchloe\xe2\x80\x99s Vegan Meal for 2 -- available to order now on shop.wfm.com (link in bio!). Get the recipe for the cake below! #WFMxChefChloe #Sponsored

Vegan Pumpkin Marble Cake (Makes 1 loaf)
Ingredients: 
- 2 cups 365 All-Purpose Flour 
- 1 cup 365 Organic Cane Sugar 
- 1 teaspoon 365 Baking Powder
- 1 teaspoon sea salt
- \xc2\xbd teaspoon 365 Baking Soda
- 1 tablespoon pumpkin pie spice
- 1 cup canned pumpkin puree (or sweet potato puree)
- 1 cup 365 unsweetened Coconut Cream, mixed well before measuring
- \xc2\xbd cup 365 Organic Coconut Oil, melted
- 1 tablespoon apple cider vinegar 
- 1 tablespoon pure vanilla extract
- 3 tablespoons unsweetened cocoa powder
- \xc2\xbd cup vegan chocolate chips (optional)
- 365 Non-Dairy Plant-Based whipped cream or powdered sugar, for topping

Instructions:
Preheat the oven to 350 degrees. Lightly grease a large loaf pan and/or line with parchment. 

Whisk flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, baking soda, and pumpkin pie spice. In another bowl, whisk together pumpkin puree, coconut cream, coconut oil, vinegar, and vanilla. Pour the wet mixture into the dry mixture and whisk until just combined (don\xe2\x80\x99t overmix!). 

Transfer \xc2\xbd cup batter into a small bowl and stir in cocoa powder and 2 tablespoons water until incorporated. 

Fill the prepared pan with alternating dollops of pumpkin batter and chocolate batter. Sprinkle in chocolate chips, if using. Using a thin knife or chopstick, gently swirl the chocolate batter into the pumpkin batter. Bake for ~60 minutes. Let cool and slice. Top each slice with 365 by Whole Foods Market Non-Dairy Whipped Cream or powdered sugar."

b'With wine or without, the Spring Sparkler is bright and bursting with the flavors of the season. In just 15 minutes, you and your quaranteam can kick back by the grill with these zesty, homemade drinks in hand. Don\xe2\x80\x99t skimp on Whole Trade pineapple \xe2\x80\x94 you\xe2\x80\x99ll want something to snack on when your glass is empty. Full recipe :backhand_index_pointing_down: 
Serves 8 
Ingredients:
- 4 green tea bags
- 2 cups 1-inch pineapple chunks, plus more for garnish
- 1 (750-ml) bottle chardonnay, divided
- 2 cups blood orange Italian soda 
Method:
- Steep tea in 1 cup boiling water for 10 minutes.
- Pur\xc3\xa9e pineapple and half of the wine in a blender until very smooth.
- Strain through a fine sieve into a large pitcher; discard any solids.
- Discard tea bags and add tea to pitcher, along with remaining wine.
- Stir, pour over ice and top off with soda.
- Garnish with pineapple and serve. 
Must be 21+. Please drink responsibly.'
